-- Lilly profits rise on fast-growing drugs
-- 
-- Mon Apr 21, 2008 6:54am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/04/21/us-lilly-results-idUSWNAS851120080421

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Eli Lilly and Co ( LLY.N ) said on Monday its first-quarter earnings rose on higher sales of its treatments for diabetes, cancer and depression. 

 The Indianapolis-based drugmaker earned $1.06 billion, or 97 cents a share, compared with $508.7 million, or 47 cents per share, in the year-earlier period. (Reporting by  Euan Rocha  and Ransdell Pierson; Editing by  Derek Caney )